- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the article discusses the use of tools for automated configuration and installation, which involves networking and communication between different components. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the article discusses the design and development of a fabric management system. 
- cs.Distributed Systems is a relevant category as the article discusses the management of distributed resources. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the article may discuss the programming languages used in the development of the fabric management system.
